        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 6:47PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 647 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Detroit, or near Downtown Detroit, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Downtown Detroit around 710 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Northeast Detroit,
Highland Park, Harper Woods, Hamtramck, Grosse Pointe Park, Grosse
Pointe Farms, Grosse Pointe Woods, and Grosse Pointe Shores.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
